text-unit.text:
For TUGboat, we prefer not to print the ‘https://’, but to include the protocol in other cases, so we usually do 

 \def\url{\tburl}

, which takes care of that, while keeping the source using the standard \url command.

For an em-dash with our spacing (preferred to 

 ---

): \Dash, with output — like this.

For initialisms in all caps: 

 \acro{FRED}

,with output: FRED.

A title: 

 \titleref{Book of Fred}

,with output: Book of Fred.
